\begin{align*}f(x)=\frac{2x^3}{3x^2-9}\end{align*}

Its first and second derivatives are given by

\begin{align*}f'(x)=\frac{2x^2(x^2-9)}{3(x^2-3)^2},\qquad{}f''(x)=\frac{4x(x^2+9)}{(x^2-3)^3}\end{align*}

